# Agent Rules: [PROJECT NAME]

> House rules for how agents behave in this repository.

---

## Code Style

- Follow [style guide name] conventions
- Use [indentation: tabs/spaces, width]
- Maximum line length: [number or "no limit"]
- File maximum: [number] lines

## Git Conventions

- Commit format: `<type>: <description>` (e.g., `feat: add login endpoint`)
- Types: feat, fix, refactor, docs, test, chore, perf, ci
- Branch naming: `[type]/[short-description]` (e.g., `feat/user-auth`)
- Never force-push to main
- Never commit directly to main without PR

## Before Every Commit

- [ ] Tests pass
- [ ] Linter passes
- [ ] No new warnings
- [ ] No secrets or credentials in code

## Review Requirements

- All PRs require at least [number] review(s)
- Security-related changes require security review
- Database schema changes require migration review

## Things Agents Must Never Do

- **Never hardcode secrets or credentials** — use environment variables
- **Never modify production database directly** — use migrations
- **Never skip tests to make a build pass** — fix the tests
- **Never commit .env files** — they contain secrets
- **Never override a human's explicit decision** — ask first

## Communication

- If you're unsure about a decision, ask the human
- If you find a bug you didn't cause, report it
- If a task is outside your scope, say so
- Always explain why you made a non-obvious choice
